Liverpool summer signing Divock Origi stole the show at Stade Pierre-Mauroy on Sunday afternoon as the striker scored and claimed an assist for Lille in their Ligue 1 match against Nantes.

Origi, who sealed a £10million switch to Anfield in the summer before rejoining Lille on season-long loan deal, scored just after the interval to put his side 1-0 up.

Lille's teenage forward leapt above Nantes' defence to nod home from close range after getting on the end of a cross from team-mate Florent Balmont.

